io.confluent.ksql.planner.plan

Class KeyConstraint

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.confluent.ksql.planner.plan.KeyConstraint
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    LookupConstraint

    public class KeyConstraint
extends java.lang.Object
implements LookupConstraint
    An instance of this class represents what we know about the use of keys in a given disjunct from an expression. The key's value, operator associated with it, and window bounds are available through the given methods. These are used as hints for the physical planning layer about how to fetch the corresponding rows.
